data.name: device_config
data.value: <?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?> <DeviceConfiguration xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema"> <SyncPatterns> <SyncPattern> <Identifier>itunes-style</Identifier> <Name>Arist\Album\Tracks</Name> <Pattern>%ARTIST%\%ALBUM%\%TRACKNUMSPACE%%NAME%</Pattern> <Description>This pattern places the tracks the same way iTunes places tracks in a managed iTunes music folder. Files are organized by Artist\Album\TrackNumber Name. This pattern is recommended for the Sony Ericsson W800i (Walkman phone).</Description> <CompilationsPattern>Compilations\%ALBUM%\%TRACKNUMSPACE%%NAME%</CompilationsPattern> </SyncPattern> <SyncPattern> <Identifier>one-folder</Identifier> <Name>Artist\Tracks</Name> <Pattern>%ARTIST% - %ALBUM%\%TRACKNUMSPACE%%NAME%</Pattern> <Description>This pattern organizes the tracks in folders named by Artist and album. Files are organized like this: Artist - Album\TrackNumber Name.</Description> <CompilationsPattern>%ALBUM%\%TRACKNUMSPACE%%NAME%</CompilationsPattern> </SyncPattern> <SyncPattern> <Identifier>flat</Identifier> <Name>All tracks in one folder</Name> <Pattern>%ARTIST% - %NAME%</Pattern> <Description>This pattern organizes all tracks in the root media folder of the device. All tracks from all artists are in one folder and names like this: Artist - Name.</Description> <CompilationsPattern /> </SyncPattern> </SyncPatterns> <Devices> <Device> <Name>My iCherry</Name> <MediaRoot>Music</MediaRoot> <SyncPattern>itunes</SyncPattern> <RecognizePattern>icherry.np</RecognizePattern> <Playlist /> <InitialTracks /> </Device> </Devices> </DeviceConfiguration>

data.name: logging
data.value:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?> <log4net> <appender name="LogFile" type="log4net.Appender.FileAppender"> <file value="icherrymm.log" /> <appendToFile value="true" />
<layout type="log4net.Layout.PatternLayout"> <conversionPattern value="%5level [%thread] (%logger:%line) - %message%newline" /> </layout> </appender>
<root> <level value="INFO" /> <appender-ref ref="LogFile" /> </root> </log4net>
